UML:TaggedValue.value: Earth Observation Products application schema, also the base schema which other products, OPT, ATM etc., extend.
Spectral band present in the product
Individual wavelengths measured. Note this is optional.
End of the observed wavelength range
Start of the observed wavelength range
Spacing between consecutive wavelengths. Note this is optional.

Mask defined as a feature collection (in the GML 3.2 sense : a feature collection is a feature having a property derived by extension from gml:AbstractFeatureMemberType). Mandates the following optional gml properties inherited from gml:AbstractFeature : - gml:id attribute - gml:name - gml:boundedBy
Mask member : . Mandates the following optional gml properties inherited from gml:_Feature : - gml:id attribute - gml:name - gml:boundedBy
Type of sensor, corresponds to EOP Product types
Enumeration to indicate direction of orbit pass
Information about the processing date, methods and processing centre.
Composite type of product, if available
Method used to compute datalayer. (e.g. Kalman filtering, ROSE)
Processing centre code. Possible values are mission specific and should be retrieved using codespace.
Processing level applied to the product

Processing mode. Often referred to as Real Time, Near Real Time etc. Should be a value from ProcessingModeValue. As the precise definitions of these terms vary, this enumeration uses more generic terms.
Sensor mode. Possible values are mission specific and should be retrieved using codespace. (eg. PHR : PA, XS or PX).
Type of sensor, must be from codelist SensorTypeValue
Swath identifier (e.g. Envisat ASAR has 7 distinct swaths (I1,I2,I3...I7) that correspond to precise incidence angles for the sensor). Value list can be retrieved with codeSpace.
Information about the observed spectral bands
UTC date and time at ascending node of orbit
Longitude at ascending node of orbit. should be expressed in degrees.
Completion time of acquisition in milliseconds from Ascending node date.
Start time of acquisition in milliseconds from Ascending node date.
Neutral wrsLatitudeGrid to replace frame in track/frame, J in K/J, etc. The optional attribute "codeSpace" is used to point the reference grid.
Neutral wrsLongitudeGrid to replace track in track/frame, K in K/J, etc. The optional attribute "eop:codeSpace" is used to point the reference grid.
Mean illumination/solar azimuth angle given in degrees.
Mean illumination/solar zenith angle given in degrees.
Minimum illumination/solar elevation angle given in degrees.
Mean instrument azimuth angle given in degrees.
Mean instrument zenith angle given in degrees.
Mean instrument elevation angle given in degrees.
Global Incidence angle given in degrees
Instrument across track Incidence angle given in degrees.
Instrument along track incidence angle given in degrees.
List of terms to describe the method used to calculate thequality degradation percentage.
Indicatesthe quality degradation percentage has been calculated automatically.
Indicatesthe quality degradation percentage has been calculated manually.
Archiving centre code. Possible values are mission specific and should be retrieved using codespace.
Local archiving id as created by the mission ground segment that may required to allow subsequent order processing.

The Observations and Measurements (ISO 19156) observedProperty may be a reference to any type. A useful model is the SWE Phenomenon from SWE Common 1.0 The observedProperty may describe the geophysical or biophysical measurements available in the product. E.g. Sea Surface Heights, Significant Wave Heights. Ozone concentration, NDVI Multiple properties may be described by the SWE CompoundPhenomenon
Suitable values for the mask type.
Information about the available data product

Contains parameter information about any measured parameters e.g. sea surface height In the OandM model this is the 'observedProperty' The ParameterInformation class is used to allow grouping of units of measure with the SWE Phenomonon.
Reference to coverage exploitation metadata (domainSet, RangeType, ...) as offered by a corresponding WCS using a HTTP GET encoded DescribeCoverage Request.
Processing mode. Often referred to as Real Time, Near Real Time etc. As the precise definitions of these terms vary, this enumeration uses more generic terms.
Information about the data browse resource (may be a WMS or WCS for example).

An OWS ServiceReference containing links to the service delivering a browse image. This service could be any kind of URL - e.g. direct link to the image or WMS/WCS interface, it is assumed that if a client is prepared to "manage" a product delivered by such a service. The ServiceReference will also contain any XML message required for XML SOAP or POST access if applicable.

Indicates if browse is geo-referenced, and thus can be assumed to be displayed directly on a map (in which case should point to a code space for the CRS), when not supplied it is assumed that the browse is provided in "raw" satellite frame of reference.
Value is mission specific. Value list can be retrieved with codeSpace. Not used by PHR. For MODIS : OPTICAL, THERMAL
Browse type. Possible values are : THUMBNAIL, QUICKLOOK and ALBUM.
Histrogram specific : identifier of the spectral band used to compute histogram values
Container for ad-hoc metadata that does not merit a mission specific schema or extension, the localAttribute describes the name of the attribute
Container for ad-hoc metadata that does not merit a mission specific schema or extension, the localAttribute describes the value of the attribute
List of valid terms for the BrowseType
A quicklook view of the data
A small thumbnail image of the data.
A multi-image view of the data
Enumeration to indicate whether the orbit is classified as a Low Earth Orbit or Geosynchronous Earth Orbit.
High level characterisation of main mission types (GEO/LEO).

Enumeration of valid values for AquisitionType. AcquisitionType is used to distinguish at a high level the appropriateness of the acquisition for "general" use, whether the product is a nominal acquisition, special calibration product or other.
Indicates the acquisition is a calibration product
Indicates the acquisition is a nominal acquisition
Indicates some other type of acquisition
Information about the data mask (if present)

An OWS ServiceReference containing links to the service delivering the mask. In the case of a RASTER mask this may contain a direct link to the image or a WMS/WCS interface; in the case of a VECTOR mask the Service Reference may contain a direct link to the file or WFS interface. The ServiceReference will also contain any XML message required for XML SOAP or POST access if applicable.
Mask format. Possible values are : RASTER or VECTOR.

Indicates if mask is geo-referenced, and thus can be assumed to be displayed directly on a map (in which case should point to a code space for the CRS), when not supplied it is assumed that the mask is provided in "raw" satellite frame of reference.
Mask type. Possible values are : SNOW, CLOUD and QUALITY.
Allows to further specify the type of mask. Possible values are mission specific. The value list can be retrieved through the specified codeSpace.
Contains inline encoded mask polygon geometries using the gml:MultiSurface/gml:SurfaceMembers/gml:Polygon constructs.
Product metadata, about the data file.

An OWS ServiceReference containing links to the service delivering the product data. This service could be any kind of URL - e.g. direct link to the image or WMS/WCS interface, it is assumed that if a client is prepared to "manage" a product delivered by such a service. The ServiceReference will also contain any XML message required for XML SOAP or POST access if applicable.
Indicates if product is geo-referenced, (in which case should point to a code space for the CRS), when not supplied it is assumed that the browse is provided in "raw" satellite frame of reference.
Product size (bytes) allowing the user to realise how long a download is likely to take.

Timeliness of the product, such as "near real time", "rush". Possible values are mission specific and shall refer to mission/ground segment dedicated codeSpace. Example of values could be "NRT", "NOMINAL", "NTC" or "STC"
Possible values for the orientation of the Footprint polygon.
Mask member : . Mandates the following optional gml properties inherited from gml:_Feature : - gml:id attribute - gml:name - gml:boundedBy
Mask type. Value list can be retrieved with codeSpace
Mask member extent. Expected structure is gml:Polygon/gml:exterior/gml:LinearRing/gml:posList with 0 to n gml:Polygon/gml:interior/gml:LinearRing/gml:posList elements representing the holes.
Data acquisition passed a quality check with success
Data acquisition passed a quality check and degradations were found.
Codelist, whether the data is a raster or vector format
Data acquisition with known quality problems. Deprecated.
Data acquisition has been rejected for whatever reason
Information about the equipment used in the data acquisition
Information about the geographic footprint of the data collection
Acquisition center coordinates. Expected structure is gml:Point/gml:pos.

Acquisition footprint coordinates, described by a closed polygon (last point=first point), using CRS:WGS84, Latitude,Longitude pairs (per-WGS84 definition of point ordering, not necessarily per all WFS implementations). Expected structure is gml:Polygon/gml:exterior/gml:LinearRing/gml:posList.

Determines the orientation of the polygon coordinates for the exterior boundary. Possible values are CW (clockwise) or CCW (counter-clockwise) or OTHER (unspecified). Default value is counter clockwise. Element is only to be provided for products that do not follow the OGC simple features convention.
Information about the the downlinking (to earth) of the data.
Acquisition / receiving station code. Possible values are mission specific and should be retrieved using codespace.
Additional external metadata about the data acquisition.
The broad value is however too restrictive, so mission specific type definition should refer to mission/ground segment dedicated codeSpace.

Used to distinguish at a high level the appropriateness of the acquisition for "general" use, whether the product is a nominal acquisition, special calibration product or other. Values: NOMINAL, CALIBRATION, OTHER
Link to an EO product that is part of this EO product (e.g. a phr:DataStrip is composed of one or more phr:Scene)
Digital Object Identifier identifying the product (see http://www.doi.org).
Identifier for metadata item, includes ground segment namespace to guarantee uniqueness within EOP.
Creation/modification date of the catalogue entry.

Date of the last modification to the metadata item. When retrieved from a metadata catalogue, the modificationDate is the date when the metadata item was last modified (i.e. updated) in the catalogue.

Indicator to know how the quality degradation percentage has been calculated. Deprecated.
Value : AUTOMATIC, MANUAL

Contains further textual information concerning the quality degradation. It shall be provided if eop:imageQualityStatus value is DEGRADED. Possible values are mission specific and should refer to mission/ground segment dedicated codeSpace. Example of values could be "RADIOMETRY" or "GEOLOCATION".
Deprecated.
inv: if self.imageQualityStatus='DEGRADED' then self.imageQualityDegradationTag <> null
URL reference (xlink:href) to an external quality report file. This element is deprecated. Please use the equivalent productQualityReport element instead.

UML:Comment.name: Values: iso19136_2007 | iso19139_2007 | iso19136_2007_INSPIRE_Extensions Default: iso19136_2007 Description: XML Schema encoding rule to apply

UML:TaggedValue.value:
Indicator that specifies whether the product quality is degraded or not. This optional field shall be provided if the product has passed a quality check. Values: DEGRADED, NORMAL
This element is deprecated. Please use the equivalent productQualityStatus element instead
Specify a link to another EO product (e.g. ERS1 and ERS2 interferometric pair).

Indicator to know how the quality degradation percentage has been calculated.
Value : AUTOMATIC, MANUAL

Contains further textual information concerning the quality degradation. It shall be provided if eop:productQualityStatus value is DEGRADED. Possible values are mission specific and should refer to mission/ground segment dedicated codeSpace. Example of values could be "RADIOMETRY" or "GEOLOCATION".
inv: if self.imageQualityStatus='DEGRADED' then self.imageQualityDegradationTag <> null
URL reference (xlink:href) to an external quality report file.

UML:Comment.name: Values: iso19136_2007 | iso19139_2007 | iso19136_2007_INSPIRE_Extensions Default: iso19136_2007 Description: XML Schema encoding rule to apply

UML:TaggedValue.value: Indicator that specifies whether the product quality is degraded or not. This optional field shall be provided if the product has passed a quality check. Values: DEGRADED, NORMAL
Describes product type in case that mixed types are available within a single collection, this is ground segment specific definition.
Refers to product status. Values : ARCHIVED, ACQUIRED, CANCELLED, FAILED, PLANNED, POTENTIAL, REJECTED
This field refers to the eop:status value. It should be used to motivate the reason of a failure deletion or rejection
Refines the status of a product, when the value of status is ARCHIVED. It can assume two values: ON-LINE / OFF-LINE.
Link to the "father" EO product (e.g. a phr:Scene is a subset of a phr:DataStrip).
Information about any observed parameters. e.g. Sea Surface Height.

Units of measure for the observed phenomenon. Note that for a multi-faceted Constrained or Composite Phenomenon multiple unitOfMeasure attributes must be present and the unitOfMeasure element order must correspond to the order of the phenomenon descriptions.

A SWE 1.0 Phenomenon. Could be a single SWE Phenomenon (such as Sea Surface Height) or a SWE ConstrainedPhenomenon, such as a list of particular radiance bands, or a SWECompositePhenomeon which groups several discrete phenomena.
Data acquisition passed a quality check with success
Data acquisition passed a quality check and degradations were found.
